Development (DEV)
Purpose:
•	Active development, initial validation, and fast feedback.
How it works:
1.	Code Commit & PR:
o	Developers push code to feature branches and open Pull Requests (PRs) against main.
2.	GitHub Actions Trigger:
o	On PR or merge to main, GitHub Actions (using GitHub-hosted runners) automatically run:
	Linting
	Unit tests (with mocked upstream services)
	Integration tests (with upstream SI microservice)
	Static analysis (e.g., Codacy(Mycro Service) and SonarQube(UI+BFF))
3.	Terraform Plan:
o	If infrastructure changes are detected, a terraform plan is run (but not applied).
4.	Feedback:
o	Results are posted to the PR for developer review.
Access Control:
•	Restricted to developers
Automation:
•	All steps are automated via GitHub Actions.
•	No manual approvals required at this stage.
